    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Traditionally refers to the culture, style, and period of the ancient vassal state or regional dynasty of Chu (770-223 BCE), which began as a duke state under the Western Zhou before expansion. Chu eventually fell to the Qin dynasty. Its center was in present-day Anhui province.</Note_Text>
